    <p>Lab1</p>
    <p>Vasya is in the third grade and now he is studying "Simple fractions with natural numerators and denominator". It turns out that a fraction is called regular if its numerator is less than the denominator, and irreducible if the numerator and denominator are mutually prime. Vasya is very fond of mathematics and therefore he solves many problems at home. At the moment, Bob is looking for the largest regular irreducible fraction, whose sum of the numerator and denominator is N.</p>
