    <p>Lab2</p>
    <p>
        It is necessary to calculate the number of N-digit numbers in a number system with base K, such that their notation does not contain two consecutive zeros.
        Input
        The two natural numbers N and K in decimal notation (2 ≤ K ≤ 10; 2 ≤ N; 4 ≤ N+K ≤ 18).
        Output
        An integer in decimal notation is the answer to the problem.
    </p>
