    <p>Lab3</p>
    <p>On a standard chessboard (8x8) there are 2 chess knights: red and green. Usually they gallop carelessly across the expanses of the board, pinching the chessboard, but today is a special day: the green horse has a birthday. The Green Horse decided to celebrate this event with the Red Horse. But to carry out this wonderful plan, they need to be on the same cage. Note that red and green chess knights are very different from black and white: they do not move alternately, but simultaneously, and if they find themselves on the same cage, no one eats anyone. How many moves do they need to enjoy the holiday?</p>
